By: Senator Corderman
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Budget and Taxation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Public School Construction – Funding
3 FOR the purpose of codifying certain provisions of law specifying the intent of the General
4 Assembly regarding funding for public school construction and increasing the annual
5 funding goal beginning in a certain fiscal year; and generally relating to funding for
6 public school construction.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Education
9 Section 5–303(m)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
13 Chapter 32 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2022, as amended by Chapter 354
14 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2024
15 Section 4
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Education
19 5–303.
20 (M) IT IS THE INTENT OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY THAT:
21 (1) BEGINNING IN FISCAL YEAR 2027, WITHIN THE DEBT
22 AFFORDABILITY GUIDELINES, THE STATE SHOULD PROVIDE AT LEAST $550,000,000
23 EACH YEAR FOR PUBLIC SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN A
